#. Tag: title
#: indi.docbook:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running an INDI server from the command line"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While &kstars; allows you to easily deploy an INDI server; you can launch an "
"INDI server from the command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:547
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since INDI is an independent backend component, you can run an INDI server "
"on a host without &kstars;. INDI can be compiled separately to run on remote "
"hosts. Furthermore, device drivers log messages to <constant>stderr</"
"constant> and that can be helpful in a debugging situation. The syntax for "
"INDI server is as following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$ <command>indiserver</command> [options] driver [<filename>driver</"
"filename> ...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: indi.docbook:557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Options:\n"
" -l d     : Log driver messages to &lt;d&gt;/YYYY-MM-DD.islog\n"
" -m m     : Kill client if gets more than this many MB behind, default 128.\n"
" -d m     : Drop streaming blobs if client gets more than this many MB "
"behind, default 5. 0 to disable.\n"
" -p p     : Alternate IP port, default 7624.\n"
" -r r     : Maximum driver restarts on error, default 10.\n"
" -f path  : Path to fifo for dynamic startup and shutdown of drivers.\n"
" -v       : Show key events, no traffic.\n"
" -vv      : -v + key message content.\n"
" -vvv     : -vv + complete xml.\n"
" driver   : Executable or [device]@host[:port]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, if you want to start an INDI server running an LX200 GPS driver "
"and listening to connections on port 8000, you would run the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "$ <command>indiserver</command> -p 8000 <filename>lx200gps</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: indi.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid "Secure Remote Operation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suppose we want to run an indiserver with INDI drivers on a remote host, "
"<constant>remote_host</constant>, and connect them to &kstars; running on "
"the local machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the local machine log onto the remote host, <constant>remote_host</"
"constant>, by typing:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:578
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$ <command>ssh</command> -L <varname>local_port</varname>:"
"<constant>remote_host</constant>:<varname>remote_port</varname>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This binds the <varname>local_port</varname> on the local machine to the "
"<varname>remote_port</varname> on the <constant>remote_host</constant>. "
"After logging in, run indiserver on the remote host:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$ <command>indiserver</command> -p <varname>remote_port</varname> "
"[<filename>driver</filename>...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: indi.docbook:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Back on the local machine, start &kstars; then open the <guimenuitem>Device "
"Manager</guimenuitem> and add a host under the <guilabel>Client</guilabel> "
"tab. The host should be the local host (usually 127.0.0.1) and the port "
"number should be the <varname>local_port</varname> used in the steps above. "
"<mousebutton>Right</mousebutton>-click on the host and select "
"<guimenuitem>Connect</guimenuitem> from the popup menu. &kstars; will "
"connect to the remote INDI server securely. The host information will be "
"saved for future sessions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
